## Statement of Purpose (English)

My family currently resides in Japan, and I need to visit them frequently.  
My eldest son (Du Jingzhe, registered at school as “ト・キョウテツ”) is enrolled in a Japanese elementary school, and my spouse (Wang Huimin, Japanese name: オウ・ケイミン) is attending a vocational school.  
In the past, I also held a Business Manager Visa and operated a business in Japan under the name “ト・ショウタイ,” which demonstrates my established and legitimate ties with Japan.  

Until now, I have been visiting Japan with single-entry temporary visitor visas. However, in order to support my family’s daily life and education, I need to visit Japan multiple times each year.  
Therefore, I am applying for a **3-year multiple-entry temporary visitor visa** to make these visits more efficient and stable.  

